GeneralExplanationGrp.MediumExplanationTxt: Addition to Statement 9:Fair Market Value of 50% Interest in Marlow-Burns LLC: Fritz B. Burns Foundation has reported a Fair Market Value for its investment in Marlow Burns, LLC as $-0- as of September 30, 2018. During the year ended September 30, 2015, Fritz B. Burns Foundation transferred a 5% interest from its 38.169% interest in Royal Palms Investment Company partnership to Marlow-Burns LLC. The organization acquired a 50% interest in Marlow-Burns LLC as a result of the transfer. An additional partner in Royal Palms Investment Company also contributed a 5% interest in Royal Palms Investment Company to Marlow-Burns LLC. The partnership interests transferred to Marlow-Burns LLC were all significant assets of Marlow-Burns LLC. Therefore, Fritz B. Burns Foundation's interest in net assets of Royal Palms Investment Company have remained the same even though partially held indirectly through Marlow-Burns LLC. The fair market value of Royal Palms Investment Company was appraised during the year ended September 30, 2014 at $5,150,000 and included the original 38.169% partnership interest (which included the 5% interest subsequently transferred to Marlow-Burns LLC). Therefore, the $5,150,000 fair market value amount reported for the 33.169% interest in Royal Palms Investment Company in this return includes the fair market value of its 33.169% interest in Royal Palms Investment Company and the fair market value of its interest in Marlow-Burns LLC. (Note: New appraisals of both investment interests will be obtained for the year ended September 30, 2019).
